{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5f665eb2-e4d8-41e3-afdb-46376722456d","content":"There's no project content in this directory, so here's the general guidance:\n\n### Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n**1. Update your test projects** — add the MTP runner and required extensions:\n\n```xml\n<!-- In each test .csproj -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n**2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`** in your pipeline YAML:\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*.Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests (MTP)'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*.Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --report-trx\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**3. Publish results** (TRX + coverage) — these no longer happen automatically:\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish TRX results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences to note\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Test runner | vstest.console.exe | Built into `dotnet test` |\n| TRX output | Automatic | Opt-in via `--report-trx` |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Result publish | Built into task | Separate publish tasks needed |\n\nUse `condition: always()` on the publish steps so results are uploaded even when tests fail.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c7140c21-6587-4bb2-bc21-c744c6350f9f","outputTokens":592,"requestId":"7C19:175BE3:261F5BA:2A2C133:69F93F3F"},"id":"87e36dc2-217d-476f-a820-afe16a44c86d","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:52:26.445Z","parentId":"29657f43-634a-4fd5-9b72-149c8f21b365"}
